7.title: Walking Wombat
7.plot: Tim Faulkner calls Chris in on the case of Kenny the Wombat, whose swelling turns out to be an allergic reaction to grass. Lisa treats Dillon, a 13-year-old dog who has swallowed a chicken bone.

8.title: Cujo the Cavoodle
8.plot: Chris checks out a young dog for his suitability to go to the hospital for his young master, a boy with Cystic Fibrosis. Andrew examines a 6-month-old Lab with a limp. Chris helps a cow with a breach birth.

9.title: Little Orphan Brûlée
9.plot: Losing his mother has put a newborn colt named Brûlée at risk, and Dr. Chris is called in to find a creative solution to help. At the Small Animal Specialist Hospital (SASH), Dr. Lisa Chimes acts fast to treat a beloved dog before it's too late. Later, Dr. Chris meets some Tasmanian devils and discusses the efforts to save this endangered species.

10.title: Dot & Dash
10.plot: Dr. Chris travels to a farm to see twin foals named Dot & Dash, who are facing very different futures when their mother nurtures only one of them. Dr. Lisa diagnoses a surprising condition, and performs emergency surgery to save a dog's vision at SASH.

3.title: Orphaned and Alone
3.plot: Late at night, a police officer brings an abandoned pair of boxer pups--one of whom has been struck by a car--into Dr. Chris's practice. Chris works to treat the injuries and attempts to keep the brothers together. Meanwhile, a beloved dog named Dora sustains a venomous bite in a battle with a snake. When Dora arrives at SASH, Dr. Lisa helps her in a struggle for her life. Also, a veterinary intern becomes attached to an orphaned newborn kitten.

4.title: In a Heartbeat
4.plot: A bond is cemented between a foster family and a tiny puppy when the pup is diagnosed with a heart condition. Dr. Chris calls in surgeon Andrew Marchevsky to see if he can operate to repair the heart. Then, Chris is summoned to the marina where a boat owner wants to evict a vulnerable family of herons who have taken over the helm of his boat. Later, an extreme heat wave could have dire consequences for a treasured pet rabbit unless Dr. Chris acts fast.
